value: Breeds in arctic North America from Coronation Gulf to the west shore of Hudson Bay (Churchill). Winters in South America to Bolivia, Para- guay, northern Argentina (Buenos Aires Province) and Uruguay.^ On migration occurs in the West Indies, Florida, western Mississippi Valley and to a lesser extent on the Atlantic coast of the United States, Central America and Mexico.

value: Sedge tundra near water, often near wooded borders of the taiga (breeding); mudflats, flooded fields, shallow ponds and pools, and marshes (nonbreeding).
